# VMware AVI — Credential Template
# The fastest path is the guided wizard, which writes this file for you (0600,
# password stored grep-safe as b64:) and never leaves a plaintext secret on disk:
#
#   vmware-avi init
#
# To set it up by hand instead:
#   cp .env.example ~/.vmware-avi/.env
#   chmod 600 ~/.vmware-avi/.env
#
# Naming convention: {CONTROLLER_NAME_UPPER}_PASSWORD
#   - Replace hyphens with underscores
#   - Convert to UPPERCASE
#   - Example: controller "prod-avi" → PROD_AVI_PASSWORD
#
# Passwords are auto-encoded to grep-safe b64: form on first load (obfuscation,
# NOT encryption). For real secrets management, inject {NAME}_PASSWORD from a
# secret manager (Vault / CyberArk / AWS SM / K8s Secret) instead.

# Passwords for controllers defined in config.yaml
PROD_AVI_PASSWORD=

# Add more as needed — one per controller in config.yaml
# STAGING_AVI_PASSWORD=
